-- Azmeel Planning Unit for Saudi Arabian Solar-Panels Plant, Al-Awsat Says
-- Mourad Haroutunian
-- 2010-07-26T06:26:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-26/azmeel-plans-400-million-saudi-arabian-solar-panels-plant-al-awsat-says.html

          
          
             Azmeel , a Saudi holding company,
plans to set up a subsidiary to develop and operate a solar
panels plant in  Jubail Industrial City ,  Asharq al-Awsat 
reported, citing Chief Executive Officer Abdulrahman al-Jabr.  
 The new company will have a capital of 1.5 billion riyals
($400 million), the newspaper said, citing al-Jabr. Production
from the facility will begin in 2012, the London-based Arabic-
language newspaper added.  
